At 16:11 7/22/2002 -0700, David Schwarze wrote:
>Showers - I must have one per day to really feel good.  If you are not 
>staying at a campground, the beach is the best place to get a free 
>shower.  In a pinch, you can sneak into a hospital or walk in the front 
>gates of a KOA with your towel in a backpack.  Many truck stops have 
>showers available for a few bucks if you're on the road.  A fitness club 
>is, as someone else already mentioned, a great idea too.
=====================>
Don't forget university gymnasiums facilities and public swimming pools.

>Food - unless you are *really* on a budget, don't bother with cooking in 
>your bus.  It's messy and time consuming and won't save you a whole lot of 
>money anyway.
============================>
Cheese, crackers, mustard, pickles, apples, = my all time reallygreat camp 
meal = easy and nice.
Cans of soup where you just heat the entire can in a boiling pot of water, 
then eat from a bowl = only a bowl to clean = use the hot water you used 
for heating it up.
Think ease of cleanup when thinking of meals, food selection, and preparation.
Breakfast = motels with the free breakfast buffet are nice. :-)

>Privacy - Get a good set of curtains that are easy to put up and take 
>down.  You will be doing this at least twice per day and if you can't do 
>it quickly it will get aggravating.
========================>
Hanging heavy count thread bedsheets or light canvas on the outside, cut to 
fit all the window sizes, and hung with binder clips is really fast and easy.

Bob Perring
